{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In summary, multimodal-based 3D-PCPR methods aim to overcome the limitations of single-sensor or single-modality approaches by fusing point cloud information with other modalities.",
    "This fusion leverages the complementary nature of multimodal information, such as Camera-LiDAR, Radar-LiDAR, and Multi-view Fusion, among others.",
    "These methods, exemplified by MinkLoc++ (Komorowski et al. 2021), AdaFusion (Lai et al. 2022), Radar-to-LiDAR (Yin et al. 2021), CVTNet (Ma et al. 2023), and others, strive to achieve robust and adaptable place recognition in complex and dynamic environments.",
    "Whereas multimodal 3D-PCPR methods enhance the robustness of place recognition, they also require careful synchronization and calibration of sensors, which can be a challenging task.",
    "Continued development in the field of multimodal-based 3D-PCPR holds promise for further advancements and improvements in place recognition capabilities."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "These methods, exemplified by MinkLoc++ (Komorowski et al. 2021), AdaFusion (Lai et al. 2022), Radar-to-LiDAR (Yin et al. 2021), CVTNet (Ma et al. 2023), and others, strive to achieve robust and adaptable place recognition in complex and dynamic environments."
  ]
